{"_id":"public/js/main.js","hash":"de64726061d74161875848f720a98089e44a5d10","modified":1665761675696},{"_id":"public/js/search.js","hash":"6384ed6eeebce38bff27510500a2482e1b2a7df2","modified":1665761675696}],"Category":[],"Data":[],"Page":[],"Post":[{"title":"first post","date":"2022-10-13T18:30:52.000Z","_content":"# WEEK 4 UX\n\n## Modelling Requirement\n ---\n### **informal method:** \n1. **user stories**\n2. **user cases**\n3. **personas**  \n    Definition:  \n    A Persona Is a fictional character created to convey(传递) a certain set of user properties and behaviours to a technical recipient(接受者)\n\n\n    \n\n\n4. **scenarios**\n    \n    Definition:     \n    A Scenario is a detailed description of the user’s interaction with the computer\n    \n\n    scenarios can be used to clarify issues and implications of system development when there is no other way to do so.\n\n\n### **semi-formal method**\n1. wireframe（线框)  \n线框图很简单，通常是手绘的，是拟议用户界面的草图\n\n\n2. mock-up and story board\n  \n  Mock-ups & Storyboards are just extensions of wireframes, but with more flesh on the bones. Again both mock-ups and storyboards may occur as hand drawn sketches, or as computer-generated interface elements. These mostly don’t have the ability to run real code – being presented mainly for their visual look and feel – indeed, both mainly sit between the wireframe and the ‘prototype’. As with wireframes, mockups are mostly a singular interface screen or component (or loosely-related series of screens) which can then be discussed\n\n3. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n","source":"_posts/first-post.md","raw":"---\ntitle: first post\ndate: 2022-10-13 19:30:52\ntags:\n---\n# WEEK 4 UX\n\n## Modelling Requirement\n ---\n### **informal method:** \n1. **user stories**\n2. **user cases**\n3. **personas**  \n    Definition:  \n    A Persona Is a fictional character created to convey(传递) a certain set of user properties and behaviours to a technical recipient(接受者)\n\n\n    \n\n\n4. **scenarios**\n    \n    Definition:     \n    A Scenario is a detailed description of the user’s interaction with the computer\n    \n\n    scenarios can be used to clarify issues and implications of system development when there is no other way to do so.\n\n\n### **semi-formal method**\n1. wireframe（线框)  \n线框图很简单，通常是手绘的，是拟议用户界面的草图\n\n\n2. mock-up and story board\n  \n  Mock-ups & Storyboards are just extensions of wireframes, but with more flesh on the bones. Again both mock-ups and storyboards may occur as hand drawn sketches, or as computer-generated interface elements. These mostly don’t have the ability to run real code – being presented mainly for their visual look and feel – indeed, both mainly sit between the wireframe and the ‘prototype’. As with wireframes, mockups are mostly a singular interface screen or component (or loosely-related series of screens) which can then be discussed\n\n3. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n","slug":"first-post","published":1,"updated":"2022-10-13T21:41:57.243Z","comments":1,"layout":"post","photos":[],"link":"","_id":"cl98nhr3i0000tenl6c185oga","content":"<h1 id=\"WEEK-4-UX\"><a href=\"#WEEK-4-UX\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"WEEK 4 UX\"></a>WEEK 4 UX</h1><h2 id=\"Modelling-Requirement\"><a href=\"#Modelling-Requirement\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Modelling Requirement\"></a>Modelling Requirement</h2><hr>\n<h3 id=\"informal-method\"><a href=\"#informal-method\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"informal method:\"></a><strong>informal method:</strong></h3><ol>\n<li><p><strong>user stories</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>user cases</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>personas</strong><br> Definition:<br> A Persona Is a fictional character created to convey(传递) a certain set of user properties and behaviours to a technical recipient(接受者)</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>scenarios</strong></p>\n<p> Definition:<br> A Scenario is a detailed description of the user’s interaction with the computer</p>\n<p> scenarios can be used to clarify issues and implications of system development when there is no other way to do so.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"semi-formal-method\"><a href=\"#semi-formal-method\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"semi-formal method\"></a><strong>semi-formal method</strong></h3><ol>\n<li><p>wireframe（线框)<br>线框图很简单，通常是手绘的，是拟议用户界面的草图</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>mock-up and story board</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>  Mock-ups &amp; Storyboards are just extensions of wireframes, but with more flesh on the bones. Again both mock-ups and storyboards may occur as hand drawn sketches, or as computer-generated interface elements. These mostly don’t have the ability to run real code – being presented mainly for their visual look and feel – indeed, both mainly sit between the wireframe and the ‘prototype’. As with wireframes, mockups are mostly a singular interface screen or component (or loosely-related series of screens) which can then be discussed</p>\n<p>3. </p>\n","site":{"data":{}},"excerpt":"","more":"<h1 id=\"WEEK-4-UX\"><a href=\"#WEEK-4-UX\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"WEEK 4 UX\"></a>WEEK 4 UX</h1><h2 id=\"Modelling-Requirement\"><a href=\"#Modelling-Requirement\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Modelling Requirement\"></a>Modelling Requirement</h2><hr>\n<h3 id=\"informal-method\"><a href=\"#informal-method\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"informal method:\"></a><strong>informal method:</strong></h3><ol>\n<li><p><strong>user stories</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>user cases</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>personas</strong><br> Definition:<br> A Persona Is a fictional character created to convey(传递) a certain set of user properties and behaviours to a technical recipient(接受者)</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>scenarios</strong></p>\n<p> Definition:<br> A Scenario is a detailed description of the user’s interaction with the computer</p>\n<p> scenarios can be used to clarify issues and implications of system development when there is no other way to do so.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"semi-formal-method\"><a href=\"#semi-formal-method\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"semi-formal method\"></a><strong>semi-formal method</strong></h3><ol>\n<li><p>wireframe（线框)<br>线框图很简单，通常是手绘的，是拟议用户界面的草图</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>mock-up and story board</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>  Mock-ups &amp; Storyboards are just extensions of wireframes, but with more flesh on the bones. Again both mock-ups and storyboards may occur as hand drawn sketches, or as computer-generated interface elements. These mostly don’t have the ability to run real code – being presented mainly for their visual look and feel – indeed, both mainly sit between the wireframe and the ‘prototype’. As with wireframes, mockups are mostly a singular interface screen or component (or loosely-related series of screens) which can then be discussed</p>\n<p>3. </p>\n"},{"title":"Hello World","_content":"Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Create a new post\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo new \"My New Post\"\n```\n\nMore info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)\n\n### Run server\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo server\n```\n\nMore info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)\n\n### Generate static files\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo generate\n```\n\nMore info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)\n\n### Deploy to remote sites\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo deploy\n```\n\nMore info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)\n","source":"_posts/hello-world.md","raw":"---\ntitle: Hello World\n---\nWelcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Create a new post\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo new \"My New Post\"\n```\n\nMore info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)\n\n### Run server\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo server\n```\n\nMore info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)\n\n### Generate static files\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo generate\n```\n\nMore info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)\n\n### Deploy to remote sites\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo deploy\n```\n\nMore info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)\n","slug":"hello-world","published":1,"date":"2022-10-13T14:35:03.983Z","updated":"2022-10-13T14:35:03.984Z","comments":1,"layout":"post","photos":[],"link":"","_id":"cl98nhr3m0001tenl6ngsbeel","content":"<p>Welcome to <a href=\"https://hexo.io/\">Hexo</a>! This is your very first post. Check <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/\">documentation</a> for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html\">troubleshooting</a> or you can ask me on <a href=\"https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Quick-Start\"><a href=\"#Quick-Start\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Quick Start\"></a>Quick Start</h2><h3 id=\"Create-a-new-post\"><a href=\"#Create-a-new-post\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Create a new post\"></a>Create a new post</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo new <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;My New Post&quot;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html\">Writing</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Run-server\"><a href=\"#Run-server\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Run server\"></a>Run server</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo server<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/server.html\">Server</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Generate-static-files\"><a href=\"#Generate-static-files\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Generate static files\"></a>Generate static files</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo generate<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html\">Generating</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Deploy-to-remote-sites\"><a href=\"#Deploy-to-remote-sites\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Deploy to remote sites\"></a>Deploy to remote sites</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html\">Deployment</a></p>\n","site":{"data":{}},"excerpt":"","more":"<p>Welcome to <a href=\"https://hexo.io/\">Hexo</a>! This is your very first post. Check <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/\">documentation</a> for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html\">troubleshooting</a> or you can ask me on <a href=\"https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Quick-Start\"><a href=\"#Quick-Start\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Quick Start\"></a>Quick Start</h2><h3 id=\"Create-a-new-post\"><a href=\"#Create-a-new-post\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Create a new post\"></a>Create a new post</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo new <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;My New Post&quot;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html\">Writing</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Run-server\"><a href=\"#Run-server\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Run server\"></a>Run server</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo server<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/server.html\">Server</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Generate-static-files\"><a href=\"#Generate-static-files\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Generate static files\"></a>Generate static files</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo generate<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html\">Generating</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"Deploy-to-remote-sites\"><a href=\"#Deploy-to-remote-sites\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Deploy to remote sites\"></a>Deploy to remote sites</h3><figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><code class=\"hljs bash\">$ hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>More info: <a href=\"https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html\">Deployment</a></p>\n"},{"title":"test_my_site","date":"2022-10-13T14:41:51.000Z","_content":"","source":"_posts/test-my-site.md","raw":"---\ntitle: test_my_site\ndate: 2022-10-13 15:41:51\ntags:\n---\n","slug":"test-my-site","published":1,"updated":"2022-10-13T14:41:51.616Z","comments":1,"layout":"post","photos":[],"link":"","_id":"cl98nhr3o0002tenlbctj55l0","content":"","site":{"data":{}},"excerpt":"","more":""},{"title":"reinforced_learning","data":"2022-10-12T23:00:00.000Z","mathjax":true,"_content":" \n\n# Reinforced Learning\n\nQ_learning Algorithm\n![rl_1](/blog/pictures/rl_1.png)\ns is state,  \na is action,  \n $\\alpha$ is learning rate.   \n $\\gamma$ is discount factor.  \n $r$ is reward\n\n\n\n\n\n","source":"_posts/reinforced_learning.md","raw":"---\ntitle:  reinforced_learning\ndata:  2022-10-13\ntags:\nmathjax: true\n--- \n\n# Reinforced Learning\n\nQ_learning Algorithm\n![rl_1](/blog/pictures/rl_1.png)\ns is state,  \na is action,  \n $\\alpha$ is learning rate.   \n $\\gamma$ is discount factor.  \n $r$ is reward\n\n\n\n\n\n","slug":"reinforced_learning","published":1,"date":"2022-10-13T22:23:40.562Z","updated":"2022-10-14T14:41:04.111Z","comments":1,"layout":"post","photos":[],"link":"","_id":"cl98nhr3p0003tenlefrud6co","content":"<h1 id=\"Reinforced-Learning\"><a href=\"#Reinforced-Learning\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Reinforced Learning\"></a>Reinforced Learning</h1><p>Q_learning Algorithm<br><img src=\"/blog/pictures/rl_1.png\" alt=\"rl_1\"><br>s is state,<br>a is action,<br> $\\alpha$ is learning rate.<br> $\\gamma$ is discount factor.<br> $r$ is reward</p>\n","site":{"data":{}},"excerpt":"","more":"<h1 id=\"Reinforced-Learning\"><a href=\"#Reinforced-Learning\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Reinforced Learning\"></a>Reinforced Learning</h1><p>Q_learning Algorithm<br><img src=\"/blog/pictures/rl_1.png\" alt=\"rl_1\"><br>s is state,<br>a is action,<br> $\\alpha$ is learning rate.<br> $\\gamma$ is discount factor.<br> $r$ is reward</p>\n"}],"PostAsset":[],"PostCategory":[],"PostTag":[],"Tag":[]}}